---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="After-Hours Quote Automation | CPQ Agent | Brothers Automate"
  description="An AI agent that qualifies leads, looks up real pricing, books sales calls, and pushes deals to your CRM — while your team sleeps. Built for B2B manufacturing."
>
  <Header />
  <main>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="project-hero">
      <div class="hero-bg-grid"></div>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="project-hero-content" data-animate="fade-up">
          <span class="badge">After-Hours Quote Automation</span>
          <h1>Leads at 9 PM.<br /><span class="gradient-text">Pipeline by 8 AM.</span></h1>
          <p class="project-hero-sub">An AI agent that qualifies leads, looks up real pricing, books sales calls, and pushes deals to your CRM &mdash; while your team sleeps.</p>

          <div class="hero-stats">
            <div class="hero-stat">
              <span class="hero-stat-number">35-45%</span>
              <span class="hero-stat-label">After-Hours Inquiries</span>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-stat-divider"></div>
            <div class="hero-stat">
              <span class="hero-stat-number">21x</span>
              <span class="hero-stat-label">More Likely to Qualify</span>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-stat-divider"></div>
            <div class="hero-stat">
              <span class="hero-stat-number">$24K</span>
              <span class="hero-stat-label">Lost Per Month</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 0;">Prepared for CohnReznick &middot; March 2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 01 — THE PROBLEM -->
    <section class="cpq-section bg-surface-alt" id="cpq-problem">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">01 &mdash; The Problem</div>
          <h2>What happens to a lead that hits your client's website at <span class="text-orange">9 PM</span>?</h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">It sits in a contact form until morning. By then, they've already called a competitor.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-pain-points" data-animate-stagger>
          <div class="cpq-pain-point">
            <span class="pain-marker">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <span>35-45% of B2B inquiries arrive outside business hours</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-pain-point">
            <span class="pain-marker">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <span>Average response time for after-hours leads: 12-16 hours</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-pain-point">
            <span class="pain-marker">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <span>Leads contacted within 5 minutes are 21x more likely to qualify</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-pain-point">
            <span class="pain-marker">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <span>For a typical $15M manufacturer with 40 leads/month, that's $24,000/mo going unanswered</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-callout" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p class="cpq-callout-context">For a typical $15M manufacturer with 40 leads/month</p>
          <div class="cpq-callout-number">$24,000/mo</div>
          <p class="cpq-callout-desc">in after-hours leads that go unanswered</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 02 — HOW IT WORKS -->
    <section class="cpq-section" id="cpq-how">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">02 &mdash; How It Works</div>
          <h2>Four steps. <span class="gradient-text">Fully automatic.</span></h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">Prospect visits the site, chats with the agent, and your rep wakes up to a full pipeline.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-flow" data-animate-stagger>
          <div class="cpq-flow-step">
            <div class="cpq-flow-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M8 10h.01M12 10h.01M16 10h.01M9 16H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2v8a2 2 0 01-2 2h-5l-5 5v-5z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Chat</h3>
            <p>Prospect describes what they need. Agent collects product, quantity, specs, material, timeline.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-flow-arrow">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-flow-step">
            <div class="cpq-flow-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Qualify + Price</h3>
            <p>Checks against your rules. Looks up real pricing data. Gives a ballpark range.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-flow-arrow">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-flow-step">
            <div class="cpq-flow-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/><line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Book Call</h3>
            <p>Shows your team's availability. Books a sales call directly on the calendar.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-flow-arrow">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-flow-step">
            <div class="cpq-flow-icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 4h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h2"/><rect x="8" y="2" width="8" height="4" rx="1" ry="1"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Push to CRM</h3>
            <p>Contact, deal, specs, pricing, call date, summary &mdash; all in HubSpot.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-result-card" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p><strong class="text-orange">Your rep walks in at 8 AM</strong> to a pipeline full of qualified, priced, call-booked deals &mdash; with full conversation summaries attached.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 03 — WHAT YOUR REP SEES -->
    <section class="cpq-section bg-surface-alt" id="cpq-deal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">03 &mdash; What Your Rep Sees</div>
          <h2>A <span class="gradient-text">pre-built deal</span> in HubSpot</h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">No data entry. No "so what are you looking for?" on the call. Everything is already there.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="deal-card" data-animate="scale-up">
          <div class="deal-header">
            <div class="deal-icon">
              <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 4h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h2"/><rect x="8" y="2" width="8" height="4" rx="1" ry="1"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Custom Steel Brackets &mdash; Apex Industries</h3>
            <span class="deal-stage">Qualified &mdash; Call Booked</span>
          </div>
          <div class="deal-body">
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Contact</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">John Smith</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Company</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">Apex Industries</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Email</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">john@apexindustries.com</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Phone</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">(610) 555-0142</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Product</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">Custom Steel Brackets</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Category</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">Steel Brackets</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Quantity</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">500 pcs</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Material</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">1018 Carbon Steel</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Ballpark</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value cpq-green">$8,500 &ndash; $12,000</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Lead Time</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">14 &ndash; 18 days</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Timeline</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">3 weeks</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Call Booked</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">Thu Mar 13, 2:00 PM ET</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field full-width">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Specs</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value">L-shaped mounting bracket, 3mm thickness, powder coated matte black, 4x M6 mounting holes</div>
            </div>
            <div class="deal-field full-width">
              <div class="deal-field-label">Conversation Summary</div>
              <div class="deal-field-value cpq-muted">Prospect is procurement manager at Apex Industries. Needs 500 custom L-shaped steel brackets for an equipment mounting project. Prefers carbon steel with powder coat finish. Timeline is flexible but ideally within 3 weeks. Has drawings available for the call.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 04 — SMART FILTERING -->
    <section class="cpq-section" id="cpq-filter">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">04 &mdash; Smart Filtering</div>
          <h2>Bad fits get <span class="gradient-text">filtered automatically</span></h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">Your reps only see real opportunities. Everything else is handled politely and logged.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-filter-list" data-animate-stagger>
          <div class="cpq-filter-item">
            <span class="filter-marker filter-reject">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <div class="filter-request">"Can you ship these to our facility in Germany?"</div>
              <div class="filter-reason"><strong class="cpq-red">Rejected:</strong> International shipping not supported. Logged to HubSpot as Disqualified.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cpq-filter-item">
            <span class="filter-marker filter-reject">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <div class="filter-request">"We need titanium aerospace-grade components with AS9100 certification."</div>
              <div class="filter-reason"><strong class="cpq-red">Rejected:</strong> Exotic materials + aerospace certification not offered.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cpq-filter-item">
            <span class="filter-marker filter-reject">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <div class="filter-request">"I need injection-molded plastic housings."</div>
              <div class="filter-reason"><strong class="cpq-red">Rejected:</strong> Service not offered (metal fabrication only). Politely declined.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cpq-filter-item">
            <span class="filter-marker filter-flag">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <div class="filter-request">"I need some metal parts. Not sure on specs yet."</div>
              <div class="filter-reason"><strong class="cpq-yellow">Flagged:</strong> Vague specs. Lead still captured in HubSpot for manual follow-up.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-result-card" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p>Every lead &mdash; qualified, disqualified, or vague &mdash; gets logged to HubSpot. <strong class="text-orange">Nothing is ever dropped.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 05 — ERP FLEXIBILITY -->
    <section class="cpq-section bg-surface-alt" id="cpq-erp">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">05 &mdash; Architecture</div>
          <h2>Same pipeline. <span class="gradient-text">Different ERP.</span></h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">The workflow is modular. Swap the data source in config &mdash; everything else stays the same.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-erp-grid" data-animate-stagger>
          <div class="cpq-erp-badge">
            <strong>NetSuite</strong>
            <div class="erp-status cpq-green">Connector ready</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-erp-badge">
            <strong>Sage</strong>
            <div class="erp-status">Same pattern</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-erp-badge">
            <strong>QuickBooks</strong>
            <div class="erp-status">Same pattern</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-erp-badge">
            <strong>Microsoft F&amp;O</strong>
            <div class="erp-status">Same pattern</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-config-block" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div><span class="config-key">"erp"</span>: {</div>
          <div class="config-highlight">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-key">"current"</span>: <span class="config-value">"supabase-rpc"</span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-comment">// demo mode &mdash; swap to real ERP</span></div>
          <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-key">"target"</span>: <span class="config-value">"netsuite"</span>,</div>
          <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-key">"netsuite"</span>: {</div>
          <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-key">"account_id"</span>: <span class="config-value">"..."</span>,</div>
          <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-key">"script_id"</span>: <span class="config-value">"..."</span>,</div>
          <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="config-key">"api_key_env"</span>: <span class="config-value">"NETSUITE_API_KEY"</span></div>
          <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;}</div>
          <div>}</div>
        </div>

        <p class="cpq-config-note" data-animate="fade-in">The prototype uses Supabase (Postgres) to simulate ERP data. Production swap is a config change + API credentials &mdash; no code rewrite.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 06 — RELIABILITY -->
    <section class="cpq-section" id="cpq-safety">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">06 &mdash; Reliability</div>
          <h2>Every lead is <span class="gradient-text">accounted for</span></h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">If anything fails at any step, the system catches it, logs it, and alerts the team.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-safety-list" data-animate-stagger>
          <div class="cpq-safety-item">
            <span class="safety-check">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Dead letter queue</strong>
              <p>If HubSpot is down, the lead payload gets saved to a backup database. Nothing is lost. It gets replayed when the connection is restored.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-safety-item">
            <span class="safety-check">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Slack alerts on every run</strong>
              <p>Success, failure, or partial &mdash; the team gets a notification with exactly what happened. No surprises in the morning.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-safety-item">
            <span class="safety-check">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Error classification + logging</strong>
              <p>Every run is classified (success, partial, failure) and logged to a structured sheet. Patterns surface quickly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-safety-item">
            <span class="safety-check">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Data stays in your systems</strong>
              <p>Prospect data flows directly to HubSpot and the ERP. Nothing stored in the chatbot. All API calls authenticated.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 07 — NEXT STEPS -->
    <section class="cpq-section bg-surface-alt" id="cpq-next">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cpq-section-header" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-label">07 &mdash; What's Next</div>
          <h2>Working prototype <span class="gradient-text">built this week</span></h2>
          <p class="cpq-sub">The core system is functional. Here's what's needed to go live for a client.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-steps" data-animate-stagger>
          <div class="cpq-step-item">
            <div class="cpq-step-number">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Connect Real ERP</h3>
              <p>Swap Supabase demo data for the client's NetSuite, Sage, or other ERP via API.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-step-item">
            <div class="cpq-step-number">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Load Product Catalog</h3>
              <p>Import products, pricing tiers, lead times, and qualification rules.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-step-item">
            <div class="cpq-step-number">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Configure HubSpot</h3>
              <p>Create custom deal properties, pipeline stages, and follow-up sequences.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cpq-step-item">
            <div class="cpq-step-number">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Go Live</h3>
              <p>Drop the chat widget on the client's website. Agent starts capturing leads 24/7.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-timeline-card" data-animate="fade-up">
          <div class="cpq-timeline-heading">Timeline: 3&ndash;5 weeks to production</div>
          <p>Depends on ERP integration complexity and product catalog size.<br>Happy to get on a call with your ERP team to scope it out.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cpq-contact" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p class="cpq-contact-name">James Pinder</p>
          <p class="text-orange" style="font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Brothers Automate</p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted);">james@brothersautomate.com</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ===== HERO (matches ProjectPage.astro) ===== */
  .project-hero {
    position: relative;
    padding-top: 160px;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-primary) 0%, var(--bg-surface-alt) 100%);
    text-align: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-bg-grid {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(26, 54, 93, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(26, 54, 93, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 60px 60px;
    mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, black 30%, transparent 70%);
    -webkit-mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, black 30%, transparent 70%);
  }

  .project-hero-content {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-md);
    background: rgba(237, 137, 54, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(237, 137, 54, 0.3);
    color: var(--orange);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .project-hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--orange) 0%, var(--blue) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .project-hero-sub {
